summary_diag(): basic summary of autoLIMR Markov chain outputs.

Source: R/summary_diag.R
summary_diag.Rd

Function to calculate summary statistics for autoLIMR Markov chains. Based on coda::summary() function (Plummer et al., 2020).

summary_diag(x, flow = NULL, xranges = TRUE, ...)

Arguments

x

Object of class "multi_net_output" generated from autoLIMR::multi_net() function.

flow

Character argument. By default, flow = NULL, and the convergence diagnostics are returned for each Markov chain variable. If convergence diagnostics are required for one Markov chain variable only, it can be specified as a character string e.g., flow = "Plant_GPP". We suggest leaving the default flow = NULL.

xranges

Logical argument, default = TRUE. Includes the LIM::Xranges calculated flow ranges for each flow.

...

Other arguments

Value

Data frame with each row corresponding to one Markov chain variable, and columns describing various summary statistics.
